  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "There are countless romantic movies, each bringing their unique style and flavor to the genre. Here are some of the most beloved romantic films that have captured audiences over the years:\n\n1. **Casablanca (1942)** - A timeless classic set during World War II, starring Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman.\n\n2. **The Notebook (2004)** - Based on Nicholas Sparks' novel, this contemporary classic stars Ryan Gosling and Rachel McAdams.\n\n3. **Pride and Prejudice (2005)** - A beautiful adaptation of Jane Austen's novel, featuring Keira Knightley and Matthew Macfadyen.\n\n4. **Titanic (1997)** - James Cameron\u2019s epic romance-disaster film starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Kate Winslet.\n\n5. **Before Sunrise (1995)** - The first in a trilogy directed by Richard Linklater, featuring Ethan Hawke and Julie Delpy.\n\n6. **Romeo + Juliet (1996)** - A modern retelling of Shakespeare\u2019s tragic love story, starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Claire Danes.\n\n7. **La La Land (2016)** - A musical love letter to Los Angeles with performances by Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone.\n\n8. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)** - A unique take on love and memory, featuring Jim Carrey and Kate Winslet.\n\n9. **The Fault in Our Stars (2014)** - A touching story about two teenagers grappling with illness, based on John Green's novel.\n\n10. **When Harry Met Sally... (1989)** - A witty and endearing exploration of friendship and love, starring Billy Crystal and Meg Ryan.\n\nThese films vary in style and tone, but each captures the essence of romance in its own special way.",
